# Firebase WEB app config — intentionally committed (NOT a secret).
# These are publishable client values (Google ships them to every browser).
# Loaded by app.R via readRenviron("firebase.env") so Posit Connect / shinyapps.io
# get the Firebase config from the repo bundle, with no dashboard env vars.
# Security is enforced by: Email/Password auth settings, Realtime Database rules
# (auth.uid === $uid), Firebase Authorized domains, and (recommended) API-key
# restrictions + App Check.
# NOTE: the Google service-account key (cgap-lens-*.json) is a REAL secret and
# stays gitignored — never commit it.
FIREBASE_API_KEY=AIzaSyAvLHcvRwCaxYQaRYJJZRaJR_gvleRMEbk
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=cgap-lens-2e3dd
FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=cgap-lens-2e3dd.firebaseapp.com
FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=cgap-lens-2e3dd.firebasestorage.app
FIREBASE_APP_ID=1:244670945370:web:f2bfca2fe0214fdd496063
FIREBASE_DATABASE_URL=https://cgap-lens-2e3dd-default-rtdb.firebaseio.com/
